Hell yeah they did! It's Ronald fricking Reagan!

California was a pretty reliable Republican stronghold until Bill Clinton won it in 1992, and since then, the Democrats have held it.

New York is a different story; Reagan's predecessor Carter(Democrat) won it in 1976 but lost it to Reagan in 1980. Reagan was so damn popular he swept the whole country in 1984, missing only D.C. and Minnesota, Mondale's home state, which he only lost by little under 4,000 votes. He could have demanded a recount and won Minnesota, but Reagan decided to let Mondale have it.

After Reagan, Bush Sr. held California but lost New York. He was the last Republican to win California. The next election, in 1992, Bush lost California, New York, and the election to Bill Clinton.

Reagan was the last Republican to hold New York, and Bush Sr. was the last Republican to hold California. The Democrats won New York from Bush Sr. in 1988 and California from him in 1992, and since then, California and New York have been Democratic strongholds.

All this goes to show you something I personally believe; there are no Red states, and there are no Blue states. There are only Purple states. Look at the recent election; almost every state was won by a very small margin.
